Sharista Giles of Sweetwater, Tennessee, went into a coma in December after a car accident sent her to the hospital with injuries so bad doctors thought she wouldn't recover .
Her mom, Anna Moser, said she knew her daughter would wake up even when doctors said she had a two-per cent chance of recovery .
She said she now speaks to her daughter every day and shows her pictures of her son, Leighton Isiah Giles .